body:
I was experiencing this error as well. It was preventing me from using some of the contrib rnn packages. I was also getting 

> cannot import name hashtable

which led me to this [SO post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14422976/importing-pandas-shows-importerror-cannot-import-name-hashtable).

Apparently there is some dependency on pandas that was out-of-date for me. I fixed it accordingly and now these warning are gone

`pip3 install --upgrade pandas`
